            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-19T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-19T17:00:00-05:00" n="335" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 PW/9–1945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Baruch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-19T18:00:00-04:00">September 19, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1524. Yesterday there was given orally to Bianchi substance of Deptel 8075 Sept
                    17 to London (rptd Lisbon as 1513) for communication to Ptgse Govt. You may
                    inform FonOff orally while specific alternatives proposed by them are for
                    discussion with Brit Commonwealth authorities, we have emphasized to Brit Govt
                    our support of the Ptgse desire for solution which would give effect to spirit
                    of Santa Maria agreements and that we are hopeful such a solution will be
                    found.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
